  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To reduce the risk of perioperative pulmonary aspiration of gastric contents, oral intake of
      liquids or solids is not allowed for certain periods. Recently, the ultrasound (US) is used
      to evaluate the volume and the nature of the stomach content. In its latest recommendations,
      the American Society of Anesthesiologists (ASA) shortened the duration preoperative fasting.
      The aim of the study is to evaluate the efficacy of ASA recommendations in diabetic patients
      using ultrasound (US) scanning of the stomach (antrum).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
